#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/adminarea.xml:457
msgid "Customer Groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/adminarea.xml:460
msgid ""
"Customer users can also be added to a group, which can be useful if you want "
"to add customers of the same company with access to one or a few "
"queues. First create the group to which your customers will belong, via the "
"<link linkend=\"adminarea-groups\">Group management module</link>. Then add "
"the <link linkend=\"adminarea-queue\">queues</link> and select the new group "
"for the queues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/adminarea.xml:464
msgid ""
"The next step is to activate the customer group support. This can be done "
"with the configuration parameter <link "
"linkend=\"Framework:Frontend::Customer:CustomerGroupSupport\">CustomerGroupSupport</link>, "
"from the Admin SysConfig option. Using the parameter <link "
"linkend=\"Framework:Frontend::Customer:CustomerGroupAlwaysGroups\">CustomerGroupAlwaysGroups</link>, "
"you can specify the default groups for a newly added customer, so that every "
"new account will be automatically added to these groups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
