#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/acl.xml:4
msgid "Access Control Lists (ACLs)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/acl.xml:7
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/acl.xml:10
msgid ""
"From OTRS 2.0 on, Access Control Lists (ACLs) can be used to control access "
"to tickets, modules, queues, etc., or to influence actions on tickets "
"(closing, moving, etc.) in certain situations.  ACLs can be used to "
"supplement the existing permission system of <link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-roles\">roles</link> and <link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-groups\">groups</link>. Using ACLs, rudimental workflows "
"within the system can be mapped, based on ticket attributes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/acl.xml:18
msgid ""
"As yet, ACLs cannot be created using the <link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-sysconfig\">SysConfig interface</link>.  They must be "
"directly entered into the <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</filename> file.  This "
"chapter has some ACL examples which will walk you trough the process of "
"defining ACL definitions, and a reference of all possible important ACL "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/acl.xml:26
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><title>
#: en/acl.xml:30
msgid ""
"ACL allowing movement into a queue of only those tickets with ticket "
"priority 5."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><para>
#: en/acl.xml:33
msgid ""
"This example shows you the basic structure of an ACL. First, it needs to "
"have a name.  In this case, it is \"ACL-Name-2\". Note that the ACLs will be "
"numerically sorted before execution, so you should use the names carefully."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><para>
#: en/acl.xml:38
msgid ""
"Secondly, you have a \"Properties\" section which is a filter for your "
"tickets. All the criteria defined here will be applied to a ticket to "
"determine if the ACL must be applied or not.  In our example, a ticket will "
"match if it is in the queue \"Raw\" and has priority \"5 very high\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><para>
#: en/acl.xml:43
msgid ""
"Lastly, a section \"Possible\" defines modifications to the screens. In this "
"case, from the available queues, only the queue \"Alert\" can be selected in "
"a ticket screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><programlisting>
#: en/acl.xml:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# ticket acl\n"
"$Self->{TicketAcl}->{'100-Example-ACL'} = {\n"
"    # match properties\n"
"    Properties => {\n"
"        # current ticket match properties\n"
"        Ticket => {\n"
"            Queue => ['Raw'],\n"
"            Priority => ['5 very high'],\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    # return possible options (white list)\n"
"    Possible => {\n"
"        # possible ticket options (white list)\n"
"        Ticket => {\n"
"            Queue => ['Alert'],\n"
"        },\n"
"    },\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/acl.xml:29 en/acl.xml:71 en/acl.xml:128 en/acl.xml:157 en/acl.xml:195 en/stats.xml:650 en/stats.xml:684
msgid "<placeholder type=\"example\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><title>
#: en/acl.xml:72
msgid ""
"ACL disabling the closing of tickets in the raw queue, and hiding the close "
"button."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><para>
#: en/acl.xml:75
msgid ""
"Here you can see how a ticket field (state) can be filtered with more than "
"one possible value to select from. It is also possible to limit the actions "
"that can be executed for a certain ticket. In this case, the ticket cannot "
"be closed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><programlisting>
#: en/acl.xml:81
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$Self->{TicketAcl}->{'101-Second-Example-ACL'} = {\n"
"    # match properties\n"
"    Properties => {\n"
"        # current ticket match properties\n"
"        Ticket => {\n"
"            Queue => ['Raw'],\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    # return possible options (white list)\n"
"    Possible => {\n"
"        # possible ticket options (white list)\n"
"        Ticket => {\n"
"            State => ['new', 'open', 'pending reminder'],\n"
"        },\n"
"        # possible action options\n"
"        Action => {\n"
"            AgentTicketBounce        => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketClose         => 0,\n"
"            AgentTicketCompose       => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketCustomer      => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketForward       => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketFreeText      => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketHistory       => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketLink          => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketLock          => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketMerge         => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketMove          => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketNote          => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketOwner         => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketPending       => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketPhone         => 1, # only used to hide the Split "
"action\n"
"            AgentTicketPhoneInbound  => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketPhoneOutbound => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketPrint         => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketPriority      => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketResponsible   => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketWatcher       => 1,\n"
"            AgentTicketZoom          => 1,\n"
"            AgentLinkObject          => 1, # only used to hide the Link "
"action\n"
"        },\n"
"    },\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><title>
#: en/acl.xml:129
msgid "ACL removing always state closed successful."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><para>
#: en/acl.xml:132
msgid ""
"This example shows how it is possible to define negative filters (the state "
"\"closed successful\" will be removed). You can also see that not defining "
"match properties for a ticket will match any ticket, i. e. the ACL will "
"always be applied. This may be useful if you want to hide certain values by "
"default, and only enable them in special circumstances (e. g. if the agent "
"is in a specific group)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><programlisting>
#: en/acl.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$Self->{TicketAcl}->{'102-Third-ACL-Example'} = {\n"
"    # match properties\n"
"    Properties => {\n"
"        # current ticket match properties (match always)\n"
"    },\n"
"    # return possible options\n"
"    PossibleNot => {\n"
"        # possible ticket options\n"
"        Ticket => {\n"
"            State => ['closed successful'],\n"
"        },\n"
"    },\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><title>
#: en/acl.xml:158
msgid ""
"ACL only showing Hardware services for tickets that are created in queues "
"that start with &quot;HW&quot;."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><para>
#: en/acl.xml:161
msgid ""
"This example also shows you how you can use regular expressions for matching "
"tickets and for filtering the available options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><programlisting>
#: en/acl.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$Self->{TicketAcl}->{'Only-Hardware-Services-for-HW-Queues'} = {\n"
"    # match properties\n"
"    # note we don't have \"Ticket => {\" because there's no ticket yet\n"
"    Properties => {\n"
"    Queue => {\n"
"        Name => ['[RegExp]HW'],\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    # return possible options\n"
"    Possible => {\n"
"        # possible ticket options\n"
"        Ticket => {\n"
"            Service => ['[RegExp]^(Hardware)'],\n"
"        },\n"
"    },\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/acl.xml:188
msgid "Reference"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/acl.xml:191
msgid ""
"In the example below there is a list of all parameters which can be used for "
"ACLs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para><example><title>
#: en/acl.xml:196
msgid "Reference showing all possible important ACL settings."
msgstr ""

